    <h2>5 Key Insights About Depreciation</h2>
    <div class="insights-grid">
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-num">Insight 1</div>
        <div class="insight-title">Depreciation Is Not Cash Flow</div>
        <p>Depreciation is a non-cash expense. It reduces reported income but does not directly reduce cash. This is why depreciation is added back in the cash flow statement under operating activities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-num">Insight 2</div>
        <div class="insight-title">Two Sets of Books Are Normal</div>
        <p>Most U.S. companies use straight-line for financial reporting (GAAP) and MACRS for tax returns. The difference creates a deferred tax liability on the balance sheet.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-num">Insight 3</div>
        <div class="insight-title">MACRS Front-Loads Tax Savings</div>
        <p>By accelerating depreciation, MACRS provides larger tax deductions in earlier years. Due to the time value of money, a dollar saved today is worth more than a dollar saved five years from now.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-num">Insight 4</div>
        <div class="insight-title">Land Cannot Be Depreciated</div>
        <p>Land is considered to have an indefinite useful life and does not wear out. Only improvements to land (buildings, fences, paving) can be depreciated. This is a common exam question in accounting courses.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="insight-card">
        <div class="insight-num">Insight 5</div>
        <div class="insight-title">Section 179 vs. Regular Depreciation</div>
        <p>Section 179 allows businesses to deduct the full cost of qualifying assets in the year of purchase (up to $1.22M in 2024), instead of depreciating over multiple years. It is a powerful tool for small businesses.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div class="content-card">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What is depreciation in accounting?</h3>
      <p>Depreciation is the systematic allocation of an asset's cost over its useful life. It reflects the decline in value of tangible assets like equipment, vehicles, and buildings due to wear, age, or obsolescence. Depreciation is recorded as an expense on the income statement and reduces the book value of assets on the balance sheet.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What is the straight-line depreciation formula?</h3>
      <p>The straight-line depreciation formula is: Annual Depreciation = (Asset Cost − Salvage Value) ÷ Useful Life in Years. This method spreads the depreciable amount evenly across each year of the asset's useful life, making it the simplest and most commonly used depreciation method.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How does MACRS depreciation work?</h3>
      <p>MACRS (Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System) is the tax depreciation method required by the IRS for most business assets. It assigns assets to property classes (3, 5, 7, 10, 15, or 20 years) and uses predetermined percentages to calculate depreciation each year. MACRS front-loads depreciation, providing larger deductions in earlier years. Unlike other methods, salvage value is ignored under MACRS.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What is the difference between straight-line and declining balance depreciation?</h3>
      <p>Straight-line depreciation allocates an equal amount each year, while double declining balance applies a fixed rate (2 ÷ useful life) to the remaining book value each year. DDB results in higher depreciation expense in early years and lower amounts later. Straight-line is simpler and commonly used for financial reporting; DDB better matches assets that lose value quickly early in their life.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What is accumulated depreciation?</h3>
      <p>Accumulated depreciation is the total depreciation expense recorded against an asset from the time it was placed in service. It is a contra-asset account on the balance sheet that reduces the asset's gross cost to arrive at net book value. For example, if equipment cost $100,000 and has $40,000 in accumulated depreciation, its book value is $60,000.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
<script is:inline>
(function() {
  var MACRS_TABLES = {
    "3":  [33.33, 44.45, 14.81, 7.41],
    "5":  [20.00, 32.00, 19.20, 11.52, 11.52, 5.76],
    "7":  [14.29, 24.49, 17.49, 12.49, 8.93, 8.92, 8.93, 4.46],
    "10": [10.00, 18.00, 14.40, 11.52, 9.22, 7.37, 6.55, 6.55, 6.56, 6.55, 3.28],
    "15": [5.00, 9.50, 8.55, 7.70, 6.93, 6.23, 5.90, 5.90, 5.91, 5.90, 5.91, 5.90, 5.91, 5.90, 5.91, 2.95],
    "20": [3.750, 7.219, 6.677, 6.177, 5.713, 5.285, 4.888, 4.522, 4.462, 4.461, 4.462, 4.461, 4.462, 4.461, 4.462, 4.461, 4.462, 4.461, 4.462, 4.461, 2.231]
  };

  var activeMethod = "sl";
  var bookValueChart = null;
  var expenseChart = null;

  // Method toggle
  var btns = document.querySelectorAll(".method-btn");
  for (var i = 0; i < btns.length; i++) {
    btns[i].addEventListener("click", function() {
      for (var j = 0; j < btns.length; j++) {
        btns[j].className = "method-btn";
      }
      this.className = "method-btn active";
      activeMethod = this.getAttribute("data-method");
      var macrsGroup = document.getElementById("macrsClassGroup");
      if (activeMethod === "macrs") {
        macrsGroup.className = "show";
        macrsGroup.style.display = "block";
      } else {
        macrsGroup.className = "";
        macrsGroup.style.display = "none";
      }
    });
  }

  function fmt(n) {
    return "$" + n.toFixed(0).replace(/\B(?=(\d{3})+(?!\d))/g, ",");
  }

  function calcSL(cost, salvage, life) {
    var annual = (cost - salvage) / life;
    var schedule = [];
    var accum = 0;
    var bv = cost;
    for (var y = 1; y <= life; y++) {
      var dep = annual;
      if (y === life) dep = bv - salvage;
      accum += dep;
      bv -= dep;
      schedule.push({ year: y, dep: dep, accum: accum, bv: bv });
    }
    return schedule;
  }

  function calcDDB(cost, salvage, life) {
    var rate = 2 / life;
    var schedule = [];
    var accum = 0;
    var bv = cost;
    for (var y = 1; y <= life; y++) {
      var dep = bv * rate;
      if (bv - dep < salvage) dep = bv - salvage;
      if (dep < 0) dep = 0;
      accum += dep;
      bv -= dep;
      schedule.push({ year: y, dep: dep, accum: accum, bv: bv });
    }
    return schedule;
  }

  function calcMARS(cost, macrsClass) {
    var pcts = MACRS_TABLES[macrsClass];
    if (!pcts) return [];
    var schedule = [];
    var accum = 0;
    var bv = cost;
    for (var y = 0; y < pcts.length; y++) {
      var dep = cost * pcts[y] / 100;
      accum += dep;
      bv -= dep;
      if (bv < 0) bv = 0;
      schedule.push({ year: y + 1, dep: dep, accum: accum, bv: bv });
    }
    return schedule;
  }

  function renderSchedule(schedule) {
    var tbody = document.getElementById("scheduleBody");
    var html = "";
    for (var i = 0; i < schedule.length; i++) {
      var r = schedule[i];
      html += "<tr><td>" + r.year + "</td><td>" + fmt(r.dep) + "</td><td>" + fmt(r.accum) + "</td><td>" + fmt(r.bv) + "</td></tr>";
    }
    tbody.innerHTML = html;
  }

  function renderResults(schedule, cost, method) {
    var total = schedule.length > 0 ? schedule[schedule.length - 1].accum : 0;
    var annual = schedule.length > 0 ? schedule[0].dep : 0;
    var finalBV = schedule.length > 0 ? schedule[schedule.length - 1].bv : cost;
    var rate = cost > 0 ? (total / cost * 100) : 0;

    document.getElementById("resAnnual").textContent = fmt(annual) + (method === "sl" ? "/yr" : " (Yr 1)");
    document.getElementById("resTotal").textContent = fmt(total);
    document.getElementById("resRate").textContent = rate.toFixed(1) + "%";
    document.getElementById("resFinal").textContent = fmt(finalBV);
    document.getElementById("statYears").textContent = schedule.length;
    document.getElementById("statTotalDep").textContent = fmt(total);
  }

  function renderCharts(cost, salvage, life, macrsClass) {
    // Compute all three methods for comparison
    var slData = calcSL(cost, salvage, life);
    var ddbData = calcDDB(cost, salvage, life);
    var macrsData = calcMARS(cost, macrsClass);

    var maxLen = Math.max(slData.length, ddbData.length, macrsData.length);
    var labels = [];
    for (var i = 0; i <= maxLen; i++) labels.push(i === 0 ? "Start" : "Year " + i);

    // Book values (start at cost)
    var slBV = [cost]; var ddbBV = [cost]; var macrsBV = [cost];
    for (var i = 0; i < maxLen; i++) {
      slBV.push(i < slData.length ? slData[i].bv : (slData.length > 0 ? slData[slData.length - 1].bv : cost));
      ddbBV.push(i < ddbData.length ? ddbData[i].bv : (ddbData.length > 0 ? ddbData[ddbData.length - 1].bv : cost));
      macrsBV.push(i < macrsData.length ? macrsData[i].bv : (macrsData.length > 0 ? macrsData[macrsData.length - 1].bv : cost));
    }

    // Expense
    var expLabels = [];
    var slExp = []; var ddbExp = []; var macrsExp = [];
    for (var i = 0; i < maxLen; i++) {
      expLabels.push("Year " + (i + 1));
      slExp.push(i < slData.length ? slData[i].dep : 0);
      ddbExp.push(i < ddbData.length ? ddbData[i].dep : 0);
      macrsExp.push(i < macrsData.length ? macrsData[i].dep : 0);
    }

    // Destroy old charts
    if (bookValueChart) bookValueChart.destroy();
    if (expenseChart) expenseChart.destroy();

    var bvCtx = document.getElementById("bookValueChart").getContext("2d");
    bookValueChart = new Chart(bvCtx, {
      type: "line",
      data: {
        labels: labels,
        datasets: [
          { label: "Straight-Line", data: slBV, borderColor: "#4a8fe7", backgroundColor: "rgba(74,143,231,0.1)", tension: 0.3, fill: false },
          { label: "Double Declining", data: ddbBV, borderColor: "#10b981", backgroundColor: "rgba(16,185,129,0.1)", tension: 0.3, fill: false },
          { label: "MACRS", data: macrsBV, borderColor: "#ef4444", backgroundColor: "rgba(239,68,68,0.1)", tension: 0.3, fill: false }
        ]
      },
      options: {
        responsive: true,
        plugins: {
          legend: { labels: { color: "#9aa0a6" } }
        },
        scales: {
          x: { ticks: { color: "#9aa0a6" }, grid: { color: "rgba(255,255,255,0.05)" } },
          y: { ticks: { color: "#9aa0a6", callback: function(v) { return "$" + v.toLocaleString(); } }, grid: { color: "rgba(255,255,255,0.05)" } }
        }
      }
    });

    var expCtx = document.getElementById("expenseChart").getContext("2d");
    expenseChart = new Chart(expCtx, {
      type: "bar",
      data: {
        labels: expLabels,
        datasets: [
          { label: "Straight-Line", data: slExp, backgroundColor: "rgba(74,143,231,0.7)", borderColor: "#4a8fe7", borderWidth: 1 },
          { label: "Double Declining", data: ddbExp, backgroundColor: "rgba(16,185,129,0.7)", borderColor: "#10b981", borderWidth: 1 },
          { label: "MACRS", data: macrsExp, backgroundColor: "rgba(239,68,68,0.7)", borderColor: "#ef4444", borderWidth: 1 }
        ]
      },
      options: {
        responsive: true,
        plugins: {
          legend: { labels: { color: "#9aa0a6" } }
        },
        scales: {
          x: { ticks: { color: "#9aa0a6" }, grid: { color: "rgba(255,255,255,0.05)" } },
          y: { ticks: { color: "#9aa0a6", callback: function(v) { return "$" + v.toLocaleString(); } }, grid: { color: "rgba(255,255,255,0.05)" } }
        }
      }
    });
  }

  document.getElementById("btnCalculate").addEventListener("click", function() {
    var cost = parseFloat(document.getElementById("assetCost").value) || 0;
    var salvage = parseFloat(document.getElementById("salvageValue").value) || 0;
    var life = parseInt(document.getElementById("usefulLife").value) || 5;
    var macrsClass = document.getElementById("macrsClass").value;

    var schedule;
    if (activeMethod === "sl") {
      schedule = calcSL(cost, salvage, life);
    } else if (activeMethod === "ddb") {
      schedule = calcDDB(cost, salvage, life);
    } else {
      schedule = calcMARS(cost, macrsClass);
    }

    renderSchedule(schedule);
    renderResults(schedule, cost, activeMethod);
    renderCharts(cost, salvage, life, macrsClass);
  });

  // Auto-calculate on load
  document.getElementById("btnCalculate").click();
})();
</script>

</SiteLayout>
